# Observability Conventions

When backend behavior changes, keep observability coverage aligned with existing conventions in this repo.

## Metrics naming and labels

- Reuse existing metrics in `apps/backend/src/observability/metrics.service.ts`.
- `scenario_runs_total` labels must stay `{type,status}`.
- `scenario_run_duration_seconds` labels must stay `{type}`.
- `http_requests_total` labels must stay `{method,path,status_code}`.
- Prefer extending label values over creating near-duplicate metric names.

## Logging format

- Scenario logs should stay JSON and include:
  - `scenarioType`
  - `scenarioId`
  - `duration`
  - `error` (string or `null`)
- Error paths should log with `level: "error"` and explicit message text.

## Sentry

- Capture `system_error` exceptions via `@sentry/node`.
- Keep DSN in env (`SENTRY_DSN`) only. Never hardcode secrets.
- Include useful tags/extra fields (`scenarioType`, `scenarioId`, `duration`).
